   - Current liabilities are obligations that are expected to be settled within the entity's normal operating cycle, usually within one year. In the given balance sheet, the line items under "Current Liabilities" are "Accounts Payable" and "Taxes Payable".
   - The "Total Current Liabilities" line provides the aggregate value of all current liabilities.
